=== Pretty AWS

A pretty version of aws command line tools

=== INSTALL

1. install dependencies:
  sudo gem install thor
	sudo gem install aws

2. download, build and install the gem
  git clone git@github.com:davcro/pretty_aws.git
  cd pretty_aws
  gem build pretty_aws.gemspec
  gem install pretty_aws-0.0.1.gem
  
3. create the pretty_aws root directory ~/.pretty_aws
  the pretty_aws root directory will store aws config vars

4. update the pretty_aws sample config file pretty_aws.sample.yml 
and copy it to: ~/.pretty_aws/pretty_aws.yml

=== USAGE

comes with two executables for managing rds

1.  rds-instances
2.  rds-security-groups